The paper discusses privacy-preserving benchmarking, which involves protecting sensitive data while comparing performance metrics. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of homomorphic encryption and cloud-based KPI comparison suggests a focus on database systems (cs.DB) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions statistical measures, which could indicate a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) or data analysis (cs.CY).
